tldr: The user wanted to programmatically upload their .env file to Vercel and
  then control the visibility of development tools in deployed environments. The
  assistant used  for the initial upload and then implemented a
   environment variable to toggle dev features for
  client testing on Vercel Preview deployments.
overview: The user's primary goal was to programmatically upload their
  file to Vercel. After exploring several options, the
  community tool was selected. This involved troubleshooting initial command
  arguments, handling confirmation prompts, and linking the local project to
  Vercel. Subsequently, the user requested a way to show development-specific
  features (prefill and jump to report) to clients in a deployed environment,
  controlled by an environment variable. The approach taken was to introduce a
   environment variable. The application code was
  modified to check this variable, allowing dev tools to be enabled in Vercel
  Preview deployments for client testing while remaining disabled in Production.
  The necessary environment variables were added to Vercel, and the code changes
  were committed and pushed to the remote branch.
